HEADWORD: Latria
<hw>La*tri"a</hw> <pr>(l⟦adot⟧*tr⟦imac⟧"⟦adot⟧; 277)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr. <grk>latrei`a</grk>, fr.
<grk>latrey`ein</grk> to serve, fr. <grk>la`tris</grk> servant.]</ety>
<def>The highest kind of worship, or that paid to God; -- distinguished
by the Roman Catholics from <contr>dulia</contr>, or the inferior
worship paid to saints.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Latrine</ent>⟦br⟧
